12 /* Finds the configuration at a given length along the path.
13  * Parameter curv_lgth the curvilinear length.
14  * Returns the configuration at the given curvilinear length.
15  */
16 Config DubinsPath::ConstCurvArc::operator[](const double l) const {
17  Config res;
18  if (l <= 0) res = start;
19  else if (l > length) res = end;
20  else { // l is OK, let's compute
21  const double theta = start.orientation();
22  const double delta_orient = l * curv;
23  if ( Object::isZero(curv) ) // line segment
24  res = Config(start.position() + l * Vector(theta), theta);
25  else // circular arc
26  res = Config(start.position()
27  + 1 / curv * Vector(sin(delta_orient),
28  1 - cos(delta_orient) )
29  .rotate(theta), theta + delta_orient);
30  } // end of if (l OK)
31  return res;
32 } // end of Config DubinsPath::ConstCurvArc::operator[](...) const ---

34 // Fills the different arcs of a path.
35 //
36 // The starting configurations (except the first one,
37 // which is the path's starting configuration) are given.
38 // Final configuration of each arc is either the next arc's
39 // starting configuration or the path's final configuration.
40 // Curvature are found using the path type and the maximum
41 // curvature.
42 //
43 // Parameter start the initial configuration,
44 // end the final configuration,
45 // configs the intermediate starting configurations,
46 // type the type of the path,
47 // lengths the lengths of the arcs,
48 // center the turning centers of the arcs.
49 void DubinsPath::fillArcs(const Config& start, const Config& end,
50  const Config* configs[nbConfig],
51  const Type type,
52  const double lengths[nbArcs],
53  const Point* center[nbArcs]){
54  path_type = type;
55  // sets up the extremities configuration
56  paths[0].start = start;
57  paths[nbConfig].end = end;
58  total_length = 0; // and the total length
59  // for each arc
60  for(int idx = 0; idx < nbArcs; idx++) {
61  if (idx < nbConfig) // end and next config., except for the last
62  paths[idx].end = paths[idx + 1].start = *configs[idx];
63  paths[idx].curv = turnSign(type, idx) * maxi_curv; // curvature
64  paths[idx].length = lengths[idx]; // length
65  total_length += lengths[idx];
66  paths[idx].center = *center[idx];
67  } // end of for (each arc)
68 } // end of void DubinsPath::fillArcs(const Config[], const Type, ...)

70 // Computes the different arcs of a path.
71 //
72 // The configurations are computed from the first one, the type
73 // and the deflections / length.
74 // Curvature are found using the path type and the maximum
75 // curvature.
76 //
77 // Parameter start the initial configuration,
78 // sgn the signs of the curvatures,
79 // lengths the deflections or length of the arcs,
80 // center the turning centers of the arcs.
81 void DubinsPath::computeArcs(const Config& start,
82  const int sgn[nbArcs],
83  const double defl_lngth[nbArcs],
84  const Point* center[nbArcs]) {
85  static const double PIx2 = 2 * M_PI;
86  Config q = start;
87  total_length = 0;
88  for(int idx = 0; idx < nbArcs; idx++) { // sets the arcs
89  // sign of the deflection is constrained
90  const double correct_defl = (sgn[idx] * defl_lngth[idx] < 0 )
91  ? defl_lngth[idx] + sgn[idx] * PIx2 : defl_lngth[idx],
92  curv = sgn[idx] * maxi_curv,
93  // special length for the straight segment
94  l = sgn[idx] == 0 ? correct_defl : correct_defl / curv;
95  paths[idx].start = q;
96  paths[idx].curv = curv;
97  paths[idx].length = l;
98  total_length += l;
99  paths[idx].center = *center[idx];
100  q = paths[idx].end = paths[idx][l];
101  } // end of for (sets each arc)
102 } // end of void DubinsPath::computeArcs(const Type, ...) ------------

104 /* Connects two configurations.
105  * Parameter start the initial configuration,
106  * end the final configuration.
107  */
108 void DubinsPath::connect(const Config& start, const Config& end) {
109  static const Point infty_pt(INFINITY, INFINITY);
110  const Point& start_pos = start.position(), end_pos = end.position();
111  if (! isPositive(maxi_curv) ) // If maximum curvature is very small
112  if ( start.isAlignedWith(end) && start.hasInFront(end_pos) ) {
113  const Config* cfgs[nbConfig] = {&start, &end};
114  const double lgts[nbArcs] =
115  {0, start.position().distance(end_pos), 0};
116  const Point* centers_ptr[nbArcs] =
117  {&infty_pt, &infty_pt, &infty_pt};
118  // any *s* connects, lsl chosen
119  fillArcs(start, end, cfgs, lsl, lgts, centers_ptr);
120  } else // small max. curvature but not aligned or not in front
121  setNoMove(start); // no solution -> no path
122  else { // General case (max. curvature big enough)
123  const double radius = 1. / maxi_curv; // not infinite
124  Vector start_vect(start.orientation() + M_PI_2), // normal vectors
125  end_vect(end.orientation() + M_PI_2); // at start and end
126  start_vect.multiply(radius);
127  end_vect.multiply(radius);
128  const Point centers[nbTurningCircles] // turns' centers
129  = { start_pos + start_vect, start_pos - start_vect,
130  end_pos - end_vect, end_pos + end_vect };
131  // computes all possible paths
132  DubinsPath all_paths[nbPossiblePaths];
133  int typeIdx; // for each of these paths
134  for(typeIdx = 0; typeIdx < nbPossiblePaths; typeIdx++) {
135  DubinsPath &path = all_paths[typeIdx];
136  path.path_type = (Type) typeIdx;
137  // finds 1st and last curvature signs of the path
138  const int sgn[nbArcs] =
139  { turnSign(path.path_type, 0), turnSign(path.path_type, 1),
140  turnSign(path.path_type, 2) };
141  // gets the associated turning centers
142  const Point& center1 = centers[ (1 - sgn[0]) / 2 ],
143  center3 = centers[ 2 + (1 + sgn[2]) / 2 ];
144  // gets the vector connecting these turning centers
145  const Vector centers_vect = center3 - center1;
146  const double dist = centers_vect.length(); // its length
147  if ( isPositive(dist) ) { // if circle's centers are distant
148  const double dir = centers_vect.orientation();
149  // different categories -> different computations
150  const bool typeCat[2] =
151  { (path.path_type == lsl) || (path.path_type == rsr),
152  (path.path_type == lsr) || (path.path_type == rsl) },
153  has_line = typeCat[0] || typeCat[1];
154  // proportion value depends of the category
155  const double prop_val = typeCat[0] ? 0 : typeCat[1]
156  ? 2 * radius / dist : 16 * radius * radius - dist * dist;
157  // it determines whether path exists
158  const bool no_path = (! typeCat[0]) && // OK for lsl & rsr
159  ( (! typeCat[1]) || (prop_val > 1) ) && // ! far enough
160  ( (typeCat[1]) || (prop_val < 0) ); // too far (lrl & rlr)
161  if (no_path) path.setNoMove(start); // no solution -> no path
162  else { // path exists, let's play geometry
163  // length of the middle segment (also depends of the categ.)
164  const double middle_length = typeCat[0] ? dist
165  : typeCat[1] ? dist * sqrt(1 - prop_val * prop_val) : 0;
166  // the angle between the segment connecting the circles
167  // and the orientation at the end of the first arc, idem
168  const double middle_angle = typeCat[0] ? 0 : typeCat[1]
169  ? sgn[0] * asin(prop_val) : sgn[0]
170  * (atan(sqrt(prop_val) / dist) + M_PI_2);
171  // orientation at the end of the first arc
172  const double middle_dir
173  = mod2pi(dir + middle_angle),
174  // orientation at the beginning of the last arc
175  last_dir = has_line ? middle_dir
176  : mod2pi(dir - middle_angle), defl[nbArcs] =
177  // deflections of each parts
178  { middle_dir - start.orientation(),
179  has_line ? middle_length : mod2pi(- 2 * middle_angle),
180  end.orientation() - last_dir};
181  // center of middle turn, and list of center's pointers
182  const Point center2 = has_line ? infty_pt :
183  center1 + Vector(middle_dir + sgn[1] * M_PI_2)
184  * (2 * radius),
185  *centers_ptr[nbArcs] = {&center1, &center2, &center3};
186  path.computeArcs(start, sgn, defl, centers_ptr);
187  } // end of else (path exists)
188  } else // the turning circles are equal, OK for lsl and rsr
189  if ( (path.path_type == lsl) || (path.path_type == rsr) ) {
190  const double defl[nbArcs] = {end.orientation()
191  - start.orientation(), 0, 0};
192  const Point* centers_ptr[nbArcs] =
193  {&center1, &center1, &center3};
194  path.computeArcs(start, sgn, defl, centers_ptr);
195  } else setNoMove(start); // no path possible
196  } // end of for (each possible path)
197  // the solution is the shortest path: find the best index
198  int idx, best = 0;
199  double shortest = all_paths[best].length();
200  for(idx = 1; idx < nbPossiblePaths; idx++) {
201  double current = all_paths[idx].length();
202  if ( isPositive(current) && // valid & better
203  ( (current < shortest) || (! isPositive(shortest) ) ) )
204  { shortest = current; best = idx; }
205  } // end of for (each possible path)
206  // copy the best path
207  *this = all_paths[best];
208  } // end of else (general case)
209 } // end of void DubinsPath::connect(const Config&, const Config&) ---

211 /* Finds the configuration at a given length along the path.
212  * Parameter curv_lgth the curvilinear length.
213  * Returns the configuration at the given curvilinear length.
214  */
215 Config DubinsPath::operator[](const double curv_lgth) const {
216  double l = curv_lgth;
217  int idx;
218  // search in which arc we are
219  for(idx = 0; (idx < nbArcs) && (l > paths[idx].length); idx++)
220  l -= paths[idx].length;
221  return (idx == nbArcs ? paths[idx - 1].end : paths[idx][l]);
222 } // end of DubinsPath::operator[](const double) const ---------------
